{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother would also make-- they would spin their own-- she would spin her own-- and not only my mother, but the entire village.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They grew flax.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know if you know what flax is.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they would put it in the water, soak it in the water.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then-- but it's a whole process to it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then they would break it, and they would make flax and take the flax and put it on a long-- on a long stick, like, you know, on a long stick.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in the end, my mother would have like a spindle.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And down at the spindle was a potato in order to-- for balance.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she would go like-- she would go like.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She would-- she-- she-- she-- she would take the-- the flax and pull it like.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- and then she would spin it over here, then pull it, and she would [? spin it. ?] And-- and-- and this is how she would make thread-- thread.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when she had enough thread, then I would have-- then she would-- I would keep my hands like this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And she would put the flax in my both hands because then she had to make rows.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I would keep my hands.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My-- I felt my hands are falling out from my socket because I had to keep it like this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she would make-- she would make, you know, balls of-- of-- of-- of this--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--material.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then in the wintertime, they would set up like a-- like a--",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
